     TrieFinder
---------------------

Contact: Gabriel Renaud
gabriel_renaud@eva.mpg.de


Triefinder is a software to build an index of all the tags of a certain restriction enzyme site in Refseq, Unigene and Genomic databases and query a fastq of sequenced tags to assign them to known tags in the index.

##################
##              ##
## Installation ##
##              ##
##################

Make sure the main script and worker scripts are executable:

chmod u+x mainScript.pl
chmod u+x src/mergeAnnotation.pl
chmod u+x src/readFiles.pl


Build the C++ binaries:

cd src/
make



Download the databases:

- Download the RefSeq for Zebrafish.
(for example we used wget ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/refseq/D_rerio/mRNA_Prot/zebrafish.rna.fna.gz)

- Download the Unigene for Zebrafish
(for example we used wget ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/repository/UniGene/Danio_rerio/Dr.seq.all.gz)


- Download the Genome for Zebrafish

- Concatenate all the genomic sequences for the Zebrafish chromsomes (genomic database) into a single file.


##########################
##                      ##
## Running the software ##
##                      ##
##########################

Type:

./mainScript.pl

for a list of the available options.
